LOGS COMMANDS:
//git log ( this command will show logs of oue local repository)
note :
like to see last 3 logs we can go for the below command
// git log -n (this command is used for the latest logs not entire logs)
// git log --oneline ( the logs will show in the form of single line by using this command)
//git log --oneline -n (the logs will show in the form of single line with perfered numbers of logs by using this command )
// git log --author=name (by using this command we can see the specific person logs)
//git log --author=name --oneline (by using this command we can see the specific person logs with single line)
//git log --author=name -n(by using this command we can see the specific person logs of like 3,4... n logs)
//git log --author=name --online -n (by using this command we can see the specific person logs of like 3,4... n logs with single line)
-----------------------------------------------------
this commands are for filitering the logs regarding date month year.
// git log --since=yy.mm.dd  (or) git log --after=yy.mm.dd
//git log --until=yy.mm.dd   (or)  git log --before=yy.mm.dd
//git log --after=yy.mm.dd --before=yy.mm.dd (or) git log --since=yy.mm.dd --until=yy.mm.dd
